highlight-parentheses is a minor mode to highlight parentheses surrounding point.  It is unrelated to ShowParenMode, which matches parentheses.  Instead it highlights all the parentheses that enclose the cursor.  It is available [http://nschum.de/src/emacs/highlight-parentheses/ here] and via [[ELPA]].  -- [[nschum]]

* http://nschum.de/src/emacs/highlight-parentheses/
* http://nschum.de/src/emacs/highlight-parentheses/highlight-parentheses.el

http://nschum.de/src/emacs/highlight-parentheses/highlight-parentheses.png

[new]
Try using the following to integrate highlight-parentheses with autopair mode:
<pre>
(add-hook 'emacs-lisp-mode-hook
          '(lambda ()
             (highlight-parentheses-mode)
             (setq autopair-handle-action-fns
                   (list 'autopair-default-handle-action
                         '(lambda (action pair pos-before)
                            (hl-paren-color-update))))))
</pre>
This ensures that newly created parentheses are highlighted properly.  Adapt as needed for modes other than Elisp.

